text: Someone has to make the sacrifice
Or Disenchant it
it’s really more a punisher card vs. political
How do you all distinguish between punisher and political? I’m aware of both things, but I haven’t really played either style of deck
Peoples temperament?
:P
Political is really any point of the game where a choice needs to be made among the group

Punisher cards do just that - punish opponents for doing or not doing something. Political cards attempt to influence an opponent using either positive or negative reinforcement but people are typically given an active choice.
(Probably wording that wrong)
Couldn't you argue that lethal is political because someone has to make the choice to press the big, no turn for you, button?
Only if you really wanted to squeeze it to fit your worldview.
Politics gives me a choice that effects others for the most part. Stuff like [[painful quandary]] is punisher since it negatively effects them for doing something. Same w/ Zozu type cards
